From: winstang <winstang@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 27 May 2024 08:51:19 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amd/display: added NULL check at start of
 dc_validate_stream
Git-commit: 26c56049cc4f1705b498df013949427692a4b0d5
Patch-mainline: v6.11-rc1
References: CVE-2024-46802 bsc#1231111

[Why]
prevent invalid memory access

[How]
check if dc and stream are NULL

Co-authored-by: winstang <winstang@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alvin Lee <alvin.lee2@amd.com>
Acked-by: Zaeem Mohamed <zaeem.mohamed@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: winstang <winstang@amd.com>
Tested-by: Daniel Wheeler <daniel.wheeler@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/dc/core/dc_resource.c |    3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/dc/core/dc_resource.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/dc/core/dc_resource.c
@@ -2912,6 +2912,9 @@ void resource_build_bit_depth_reduction_
 
 enum dc_status dc_validate_stream(struct dc *dc, struct dc_stream_state *stream)
 {
+	if (dc == NULL || stream == NULL)
+		return DC_ERROR_UNEXPECTED;
+
 	struct dc  *core_dc = dc;
 	struct dc_link *link = stream->sink->link;
 	struct timing_generator *tg = core_dc->res_pool->timing_generators[0];
